Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} , season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}.
Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a
#saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season with salt and pepper.

Crack the @egg{1} into a medium #bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another bowl and season with the
@salt for the breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring they're
completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the
bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3
> mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, discard the oil from the #chicken pan{}. Carefully wipe out the
(now empty) frying pan, then return to medium-high heat. Add a knob of
@?butter{} and allow to melt.

Once melted, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add a generous pinch of @?sugar{} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes}
more.

While the onion fries, in a medium bowl, combine the @burger sauce{30%grams},
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @coleslaw mix{120%grams}. Season with salt and pepper.

Just before everything's ready, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop into the oven to
warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @tomato ketchup{3%tbsp} on the bun lids.

Top the bases with half the slaw, chicken schnitzel and load on the caramelised
onion, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve the fries and remaining slaw alongside.

Enjoy!